text: Karlskrona is a town in the county of Blekinge in Sweden. It is the seat of Karlskrona Municipality. The city name means Karl's Crown in honour of King Karl XI of Sweden. The city was founded in 1680, when the Royal Swedish Navy was moved from the Stockholm area to Tross√∂ island.
